							<h2>Conflict Mineral Management</h2>
							<p>MVP developed (Quentin B Samelson - Electronics COC. Planned to be presented @ Regional Industries Solution Summit in Tokyo-June)
							</p>
							<br>
							<h3>Problem Statement:</h3>
							<p>Electronic products rely on minerals which may be extracted from conflict zones. Legislation in Europe and the US requires that manufacturers audit their supply chains and report use of conflict minerals. Companies are attempting to use certifications
								& audit processes to comply, but these are only a partial solution.
							</p>
							<h3>Proposed Solution:</h3>
							<p>Use Blockchain’s “Provenance” (asset tracking) capabilities to track and trace minerals(compliant, non-conflict) all the way from mines to smelters to component manufacturing to the product assembler. This would enable a highly validated audit.
								Further, using Watson cognitive capabilities eliminate “false positives” such as companies that appear to be smelters but are physically located (for instance) on the 18th floor of an office building.
							</p>
						</div>


